<div class="task">
    <h2>Contexual Help</h2>
    
    <p>Navigate to the @Code.Ref("ContextClass") in the @Code.Sln("Basic") solution.</p>
    
    <p>
        The class contains various ReSharper code inspections. 
        <ul>
            <li><b>Hints</b> shown as a short dotted green line beneath the code</li>
            <li><b>Suggestions</b> shown as a green squigly line beneath the code</li>
            <li><b>Dead code</b> shown as faded grey text</li>
            <li><b>Errors</b> shown as red text or red squigly lines</li>
        </ul>

        Do the following
        
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to the 2 errors and fix them. What's wrong?</li>
            <li>Navigate through the suggestions in the file and see what ReSharper is suggesting. Do you agree?</li>
            <li>Go through the hints of the file (no shortcut). Does it make sense to apply any of them?</li>
        </ol>
    </p>
    
    <div class="tip">
        <b>Note</b> The inspection options can be changed either in the ReSharper options or directly through the [Quick fix] menu. These can also be shared at solution level through source control with the new ReSharper 6.x collaboration features.
    </div>    
    
